  <h1>Crispy Salad with Mixed Vegetables</h1>
  <p>A fresh, crunchy salad packed with different vegetables and a simple dressing. Perfect as a light meal or a side dish.</p>

  <h2>Ingredients (serves 2–3)</h2>

  <h3>Salad</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>150 g romaine lettuce (or iceberg), chopped</li>
    <li>100 g cucumber, sliced</li>
    <li>120 g cherry tomatoes, halved</li>
    <li>80 g red bell pepper, thinly sliced</li>
    <li>60 g carrot, grated</li>
    <li>50 g red onion, thinly sliced</li>
    <li>80 g sweet corn (optional)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Dressing</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>40 ml olive oil</li>
    <li>20 ml apple cider vinegar</li>
    <li>10 g honey (optional)</li>
    <li>3 g salt</li>
    <li>2 g black pepper</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Optional extras</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>80 g feta cheese (optional)</li>
    <li>40 g toasted sunflower seeds (optional)</li>
    <li>1–2 g chili flakes (optional)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Instructions</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Wash and dry all vegetables well. (Dry salad = extra crispy texture.)</li>
    <li>Chop the lettuce and place it in a large bowl.</li>
    <li>Add cucumber, tomatoes, bell pepper, carrot, red onion, and corn.</li>
    <li>Make the dressing: mix olive oil, vinegar, honey, salt, and pepper in a small bowl.</li>
    <li>Pour the dressing over the salad right before serving.</li>
    <li>Toss gently and serve immediately.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>For extra crispiness: keep the vegetables cold and add dressing at the last second.</li>
    <li>Want more protein? Add grilled chicken, tuna, eggs, or chickpeas.</li>
    <li>Want more crunch? Add croutons, nuts, or seeds.</li>
    <li>Make it spicy: add fresh chili or chili flakes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Required Equipment</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Cutting board and knife</li>
    <li>Large bowl</li>
    <li>Small bowl (for dressing)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Allergen Information</h2>
  <p>Basic salad is allergen-free. If using feta, contains dairy. If using seeds/nuts, may contain allergens.</p>

</body>
